<br>
Expect to pay a small to moderate fee for the GrandMaster to hit combine, even if you bring all the ingredients with you.  Those that belly-ache about payin' a price for a &quot;simple&quot; combine obviously have little experience with tradeskills.  After 20+ studded and re-inforced Acrylia combines, I still haven't skilled up from 158  (averagin' around 65-75 percent success on studded with geerlock, and about 30 percent on re-inforced... but I've got some nice gear on my baby monkey now!)<br>
<br>
Those that haven't played with tradeskills have no clue how much time and money it takes to become a grandmaster.  Tailoring is especially hard, since none of the components are easily obtainable (you can't just walk up to a vendor, and buy 2 stacks of Acrylia pieces, and a stack of superb hopper pelts).  Smithin' is gettin' there fast, especially with the re-vamp of the trivials recently.  (Shadowscream will become the new cuss words of smiths everywhere)<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp on tradeskills.<br>
